> We like to think the sixth Spice Girl is Shawarma Spice and she spins slowly for
> hours. Sorry, is that weird? We're just so stoked for our Shawarma Spice
> Blend that we let our imagination run wild. This mixture of warming spices
> gives chicken the flavors that we crave from shawarma... but without a
> rotating spit. An easy sweet spiced pan sauce made with apricot jam gives the
> chicken even more flavor. Shawarma spices also perk up the accompanying
> almond rice while a creamy yogurt dressing over the cucumber and tomato salad
> gives the dish a cool tang. This kaleidoscope of flavors is what we want,
> what we really, really want from our dinner!

== Almond Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and half the @Shawarma Spice Blend{1/2%tbsp} (you'll
use the rest in the next step). Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup},
and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

== Spiced Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then rub all over with remaining @Shawarma Spice Blend{1/2%tbsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.
Transfer to a #cutting board{} and set aside to rest.

== Cucumber Salad ==

While chicken cooks, wash and dry produce.

Quarter @Persian cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into 1/4-inch-thick pieces. Quarter
@grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, @yogurt{2%tbsp}, a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%tsp}, and a big squeeze of lemon juice. Season generously with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Taste and add more lemon juice if desired.

== Apricot Sauce ==

Return pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add @apricot jam{1},
remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer
and cook until just thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Stir in a squeeze of
lemon juice and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @butter{1/2%tbsp}. Season generously with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, rice, and salad between plates. Drizzle sauce over chicken.
Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.